\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 3. Choose to Play Again
\fs26 \
\

\f1\b0\fs24 Once you input, the computer will randomly choose a selection of Rock, Paper, or Scissors.\
Your choice and the computer\'92s choice will then be displayed, along with whether you won the round or not, based on the classic Rock, Paper, Scissors rules.\
\
The game keeps track of statistics including wins, losses, and total games played, which will also be displayed as a summary.\
\
After the round of the game, you will be asked whether you would to play again.\
Enter \'91y\'92 if you want to play another round, or \'92n\'92 to end the game.\
If you enter an invalid input, you will be prompted to answer it correctly until you do so.
